-- Saudi's Al Rajhi Bank Q1 net profit slips 16.9 pct
-- By David French
-- Sun Apr 13, 2014 02:12AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 13 (Reuters) - Al Rajhi Bank <1120.SE>, Saudi Arabia's largest listed lender, posted a 16.9 percent drop in its first-quarter net profit, in line with expectations.

The bank made 1.71 billion riyals ($456 million) in the three months ended March 31, compared with 2.05 billion riyals in the same period a year earlier, it said in a bourse statement on Sunday.